  "response": "Class A fire extinguishers, which are designed for ordinary combustibles such as wood, paper, and cloth, should not be used on electrical equipment. Using a Class A extinguisher on electrical fires can be dangerous, as they may contain water or other conductive materials that could lead to electric shock or further damage to the equipment. Instead, Class C fire extinguishers, which are specifically designed for electrical fires, should be used.",
